<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6511/1364a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-30">March 30, 1942</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>821. Bequest Foreign Office inform appropriate Governments that
                                within next few days Italian, Hungarian and Bulgarian official
                                groups will be moved to Grove Park Inn, Asheville, North Carolina,
                                and Japanese official group to Greenbrier Hotel, White Sulphur
                                Springs, West Virginia and that new accommodations will be equal to
                                those presently enjoyed by personnel concerned.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>